Some arrived at the London Victoria office before it opened in a bid to collect documents. The queues came amid reports that the backlog in applications had soared to 550,000.  But officials were turning away anyone who wasn't travelling in the next 48 hours. Previously they have warned applications could take 10 weeks. At a bruising hearing this week, Passport Office Director Thomas Greig was accused of "failing miserably" by Commons Home Affairs Committee Chairman Dame Diana Johnson. 